/*
:name: tuple_in_port
:type: equiv
:verilog_top: top
:pyrope_top: tuple_in_port.top
*/

// FAILING regression for 2i-issues C: a tuple/struct-typed INPUT port is valid,
// documented Pyrope (docs/pyrope/06-functions.md:357 shows exactly
// `comb pick(ar:(x:u3, y:s4), cond:bool) -> (res:s5)`). It must flatten to leaf
// ports ar_x / ar_y, and the body's `ar.x` / `ar.y` reads must bind to those
// flattened leaves.
//
// Today upass.tolg hard-errors before any hardware is produced:
//   "upass.tolg: unresolved reference '___res_1' — it has no driver".
// The port IS flattened (io_meta inputs = ar.x, ar.y, cond) but the body reads
// the WHOLE tuple `ar` via tuple_get, which has no tuple driver — only the
// leaves do — so lower_tuple_get cannot resolve `ar.x`. Fix is to bind a
// tuple_get whose base is a tuple-typed input to the flattened leaf pin (or have
// upass.detuple rewrite the field reads to dotted-leaf refs). Pairs with D.
pub comb top(ar:(x:u3, y:s4), cond:bool) -> (res:s5) {
  res = if cond { ar.x + 1 } else { ar.y - 1 }
}
